    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-quality 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant is mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a factory-optioned short-shift kit. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed to the highest standard, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit, a fresh Rear Main Seal, and a new Sachs clutch assembly. The suspension maintains its factory-spec geometry with original Bilstein dampers and uncompromised bushings, providing the definitive analog feedback expected of the 996 chassis. The exterior displays flawless Arctic Silver Metallic paint with high gloss and no discernible imperfections, while the interior features supple Graphite Grey leather with zero bolster wear. This is an investment-grade example with a documented service history and no mechanical vulnerabilities.",
      "price": 43500.0,
